
                                            Emergency services say the construction worker plunged several meters from a building on Thursday afternoon.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - A man has died in Sandton after falling from a construction site on Grayston Drive. Emergency services say the construction worker plunged several meters from a building on Thursday afternoon. Netcare 911's Nick Dollman said: “Reports from the scene allege that the man fell from several floors, tragically, sustained severe injuries and died at the scene. Authorities were called there to investigate the incident.”